    "sections": [
      {
        "content": [
          {
            "component": "TextGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Text",
                "content": "# Practice\n\nIt's time to build your inside-outside vision.\n\nOver the next three days, we want you to practice asking people who are close to you, how they are doing today."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "component": "ButtonGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Button",
                "content": "Next",
                "conversationId": "relationships-insideoutside-4",
                "sectionId": "2"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "id": "1",
        "alias": "1",
        "type": "defaultSection"
      },
      {
        "id": "2",
        "alias": "2",
        "content": [
          {
            "component": "TextGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Text",
                "content": "1. First, look at them and take a guess at how they might be doing today.\n\nRemember that you need to use the awareness **inside** **you** to guess what is **inside** **them**.\n\n2. Then, ask them:\n\n”How are you doing today?”\n\n”How are you feeling today?”"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "component": "ButtonGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Button",
                "content": "Continue",
                "conversationId": "relationships-insideoutside-4",
                "sectionId": "3"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "type": "defaultSection"
      },
      {
        "id": "3",
        "alias": "3",
        "content": [
          {
            "component": "TextGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Text",
                "content": "Remember to take the time to **pause** and really listen to their answer.\n\nSome key listening behaviors you can practice:\n\n\\-Focus on listening actively to the other one\n\n\\-Ask questions if you need to, to understand what the other one is experiencing\n\n\\-Do not give advice or try to fix stuff."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "component": "ButtonGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Button",
                "content": "Next",
                "conversationId": "relationships-insideoutside-4",
                "sectionId": "4"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "type": "defaultSection"
      },
      {
        "id": "4",
        "alias": "4",
        "content": [
          {
            "component": "TextGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Text",
                "content": "You’ll find two things happen:\n\n1. You’ll discover there are times when your guess is wrong. Often, to understand and be understood we need to use another's perspective.\n\n2. You’ll find out that people love it when they are asked about how they feel **IF** the person really listens to them. They’ll feel more connected to you."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "component": "ButtonGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Button",
                "content": "Continue",
                "conversationId": "relationships-insideoutside-4",
                "sectionId": "5"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "type": "defaultSection"
      },
      {
        "id": "5",
        "alias": "5",
        "content": [
          {
            "component": "TextGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Text",
                "content": "Don't assume you can guess what's going on inside of others by just *looking* at them from the *outside*. Access the *inside* by *asking*.\n\nThe same is true for your experience - help others understand you by letting them know. Mind-reading is a useful skill, but it needs to be checked out."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "component": "ButtonGroup",
            "content": [
              {
                "component": "Button",
                "content": "More",
                "conversationId": "relationships-insideoutside-5",
                "sectionId": "1"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "type": "defaultSection"
      },
